					<img src="http://forum.opiophile.org/images/icons/icon6.gif" alt="Default" /> Re: An open letter from an ER doc to drug seekers-
				</h2>
				


						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_227030">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/Eloquent/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>CIIORNOTHING</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=aa7b608c38e68f2e80eda497569b355d&amp;p=226996#post226996" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/Eloquent/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Hey thanks Wiggle.  My folks would disagree and did nothing but bitch at me for dropping out of school.  Anway, I appreciate that.   I miss that work. Im in sales now , totally different.  Much better money but boring as hell.<br />
 <br />
And hey Raz, I hear you bro, and agree to some extent.  Most times I went to the ER it was a cry for help alright, &quot;help me stop thse fucking WD's&quot;.   And for me, Ive never had a solid source for pills and I havent done the H road yet.....trying not to.</div>
			
